ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[Their 31 July press release 98-69 of the initial Vp '98 report included
the following statement:
"As a result of illnesses caused by _Vibrio parahaemolyticus_ in Washington
last year, the shellfish industry, tribes, and health regulators
cooperatively developed a plan for protecting public health. During warm
weather periods, when _Vibrio parahaemolyticus_ thrives, monitoring and
sampling efforts increase, the industry and tribes take extra precautions
in harvesting methods and refrigeration, and wholesalers, retailers and the
public are advised to cook shellfish before eating." - Mod.MHJ
